This is for nextbite. Good to know for when we define our function for them

---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: <noreply@nextbite.io>
Date: Wed, May 11, 2022 at 7:06 PM
Subject: April 30, 2022 Fulfillment Partner Payout
To: <acehaidrey@gmail.com>


Your April 30, 2022 Fulfillment Partner Payout Statement.
Hello,

Enclosed is your April 30, 2022 Fulfillment Partner Payout Statement.
For better understanding of the statement, please reference the items below=
:


   - *Number of Orders Fulfilled:* The total orders that were fulfilled in
   the payout period.
   - *Delivery Gross Sales from Orders*: Includes all delivered, cancelled,
   and unfulfilled orders. Gross sales are not reduced by error adjustments=
.
   - *Pick Up Gross Sales from Orders*: Includes all picked up orders.
   - *Gross Sales Tax (Remitted)*: Gross Sales Tax collected on all orders
   and remitted by the online order systems platforms.
   - *Commission Cap Pass-Thru*: Nextbite passes along any moratorium set
   by commission caps in your municipality. This is the difference between
   Nextbite=E2=80=99s negotiated rate with each online ordering system plat=
forms and
   the commission cap rate that is established in your city. For example, i=
f
   Nextbite=E2=80=99s negotiated commission rate with the online ordering s=
ystem is
   30%, but the commissions moratorium in your city is 20%, Nextbite will p=
ass
   along the 10% savings to you in addition to your negotiated contract pay=
out
   rate with Nextbite. Nextbite=E2=80=99s negotiated rates with each online=
 ordering
   system vary and are subject to change.
   - *Discrepancies on Payouts*: If there are any discrepancies on the
   semi-monthly payout these will be reflected in your payout at the end of
   the month. If any additional discrepancies exist at the end of the month=
,
   please contact your Account Manager.
   - *Payout Amount*: The total amount paid out by Nextbite is highlighted
   in *green* on your statement.
   - *Payout Process*: Payouts are issued on the 5th business day following
   the 15th and the last day of the month.

*If you have not received your payout for the month, please inform your
account manager as soon as possible*.

Please note: Your Ordermark admin dashboard should not be used for
accounting purposes. Ordermark captures order totals when orders come in,
but it does not update for any events following the initial order placement
(e.g., cancelled, unfulfilled, and refunded). This means the Ordermark
dashboard normally shows order totals greater than the statement data
provided by online ordering systems delivery apps.

*Do not reply to this email*. Please contact your Account Manager with any
questions.
Thank you,

Nextbite Team

