<br>
Enclosed is your April 30, 2022 Fulfillment Partner Payout Statement.</div>
<div style=3D"font-family: inherit; text-align: inherit">For better underst=
anding of the statement, please reference the items below:</div>
<div style=3D"font-family: inherit; text-align: inherit"><br></div>
<ul>
  <li style=3D"text-align: inherit"><strong>Number of Orders Fulfilled:</st=
rong> The total orders that were fulfilled in the payout period.</li>
  <li style=3D"text-align: inherit"><strong>Delivery Gross Sales from Order=
s</strong>: Includes all delivered, cancelled, and unfulfilled orders. Gros=
s sales are not reduced by error adjustments.</li>
  <li style=3D"text-align: inherit"><strong>Pick Up Gross Sales from Orders=
</strong>: Includes all picked up orders.</li>
  <li style=3D"text-align: inherit"><strong>Gross Sales Tax (Remitted)</str=
ong>: Gross Sales Tax collected on all orders and remitted by the online or=
der systems platforms.</li>
  <li style=3D"text-align: inherit"><strong>Commission Cap Pass-Thru</stron=
g>: Nextbite passes along any moratorium set by commission caps in your mun=
icipality. This is the difference between Nextbite=E2=80=99s negotiated rat=
e with each online ordering system platforms and the commission cap rate th=
at is established in your city. For example, if Nextbite=E2=80=99s negotiat=
ed commission rate with the online ordering system is 30%, but the commissi=
ons moratorium in your city is 20%, Nextbite will pass along the 10% saving=
s to you in addition to your negotiated contract payout rate with Nextbite.=
 Nextbite=E2=80=99s negotiated rates with each online ordering system vary =
and are subject to change.</li>
  <li style=3D"text-align: inherit"><strong>Discrepancies on Payouts</stron=
g>: If there are any discrepancies on the semi-monthly payout these will be=
 reflected in your payout at the end of the month. If any additional discre=
pancies exist at the end of the month, please contact your Account Manager.=
</li>
  <li style=3D"text-align: inherit"><strong>Payout Amount</strong>: The tot=
al amount paid out by Nextbite is highlighted in <strong>green</strong> on =
your statement.</li>
  <li style=3D"text-align: inherit"><strong>Payout Process</strong>: Payout=
s are issued on the 5th business day following the 15th and the last day of=
 the month.<br>
</li>
</ul>
<div style=3D"font-family: inherit; text-align: inherit"><span style=3D"col=
or: #db0e0e"><strong>If you have not received your payout for the month, pl=
ease inform your account manager as soon as possible</strong></span><span s=
tyle=3D"color: #db0e0e">.</span></div>
<div style=3D"font-family: inherit; text-align: inherit"><br></div>
<div style=3D"font-family: inherit; text-align: inherit">Please note: Your =
Ordermark admin dashboard should not be used for accounting purposes. Order=
mark captures order totals when orders come in, but it does not update for =
any events following the initial order placement (e.g., cancelled, unfulfil=
led, and refunded). This means the Ordermark dashboard normally shows order=
 totals greater than the statement data provided by online ordering systems=
 delivery apps.</div>
